    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="889" height="846" viewBox="0 0 889 846">
      <text id="In_the_past_individuals_have_been_hard-pressed_to_finish_judging_by_the_end_of_the_day_since_the_entries_require_so_much_time_to_adequately_review._Prejudging_is_meant_to_save_time_on_judging_day_by_having_the_judges_in_certain_categories_review_the_entri" data-name="In the past, individuals have been hard-pressed to finish judging by the end of the day since the entries require so much time to adequately review. Prejudging is meant to save time on judging day by having the judges in certain categories review the entri" transform="translate(6 68)" fill="#002632" font-size="18" font-family="Raleway-Regular, Raleway"><tspan x="0" y="17">In the past, individuals have been hard-pressed to finish judging by the end of the day since the entries </tspan><tspan x="0" y="43">require so much time to adequately review. Prejudging is meant to save time on judging day by having the </tspan><tspan x="0" y="69">judges in certain categories review the entries prior to the meeting. Each judge will be able to review the </tspan><tspan x="0" y="95">entries in his/her assigned categories in the week prior to the meeting and then fill in the appropriate </tspan><tspan x="0" y="121">score sheets. On judging day at the Salon, judges need only discuss their results with the others in their </tspan><tspan x="0" y="147">assigned groups and decide on the award winners. This makes their day shorter and your job much less </tspan><tspan x="0" y="173">stressful. </tspan><tspan x="0" y="199">All but animation categories require the judge to be present to judge the pieces the afternoon before the </tspan><tspan x="0" y="225">salon. The animation teams will prejudge and meet on a video call the day of the conference opening. </tspan></text>
      <text id="Process_for_Judges:" data-name="Process for Judges:" transform="translate(0 374)" fill="#202124" font-size="40" font-family="Raleway-Regular, Raleway"><tspan x="0" y="0">Process for Judges:</tspan></text>
